Utterance.UttText: Coco constantino, 61 yrs old under Dr Hodgings, came in pneumonia and allergic reactions to penicillin when he was accidentally prescribed of penicillin for his pneumonia.
He had rashes, fever and difficulty of breathing.
He is on regular puffers and prn nebs, prednisolone on random bgls, on oral antibiotics and on antihistamine.
He is afebrile today,with oxygen at 2l/ nasal prongs. sats are all normal.
His obs are all stable, he is ambulant and self caring.
